body:
## Issue

When I use the latest buildah image, I cant perform a s2i build using the command
```
Image:      "quay.io/buildah/stable",
WorkingDir: "/sources",
Command: []string{
	"buildah",
},
Args: []string{
	"bud",
	"--tls-verify=${inputs.params.verifyTLS}",
	"--layers",
	"-f",
	"/sources/Dockerfile.gen",
	"-t",
	"${outputs.resources.image.url}",
	"."},
VolumeMounts: []corev1.VolumeMount{
	{
		Name:      "libcontainers",
		MountPath: "/var/lib/containers",
	},
	{
		Name:      "generatedsources",
		MountPath: "/sources",
	},
},
SecurityContext: &corev1.SecurityContext{
	Privileged: util.NewTrue(),
},
```

as we will get this error
```
error building at STEP "COPY upload/src /tmp/src": error determining run uid: user: unknown user error looking up user "root"
```

**Remark**: This problem don't exist using image version: v1.9.0
